Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.62,0:00:11.99,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt even Shiroe predicted this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:18.78,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I won't be able to watch \Nover them from hiding anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.44,0:02:03.75,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, when you're expecting an attack \Non a population center like a city,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.75,0:02:06.71,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,you should try to take the fight \Nas far away from it as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:07.89,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.25,0:02:09.95,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you succeed in repelling them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.95,0:02:15.58,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,the damage to the city and surroundings \Ncould make life after the battle very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.85,0:02:17.74,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.74,0:02:23.06,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,We can't use telepathy, so keep your party \Nchat open and bring Isuzu here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.06,0:02:24.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.79,0:02:35.75,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1531,1)}The Red Night
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.31,0:02:32.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.18,0:02:40.26,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy levels aren't high, \Nbut there are so many...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.88,0:02:42.76,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:45.39,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Will Roe 2 be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.82,0:02:48.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,She's stronger than we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.61,0:02:50.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This way! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:51.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let go of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.66,0:02:52.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.43,0:02:54.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.79,0:02:57.05,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They're surprisingly calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.05,0:02:58.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:02.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,The Odyssey Knights...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.06,0:03:05.16,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to fight the wyverns.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.72,0:03:08.66,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the townspeople aren't worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:10.66,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We should hurry, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:25.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.93,0:03:27.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.44,0:03:49.41,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if the battle's already started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:53.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.73,0:03:54.92,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:04:00.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I, Rundel Haus Code, \Nam here, it'll be okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.28,0:04:05.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The town of Safil, Miss Minori, \NMiss Serara, and you, Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:09.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The passionate light of my orb of love will—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.42,0:04:13.97,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Now isn't the time to screw around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:16.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.93,0:04:18.11,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.19,0:04:24.57,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.57,0:04:26.37,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A Skylark Shoes spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.79,0:04:30.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,At my level, you can't fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it'll raise your movement speed \Nregardless of bad terrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.31,0:04:35.04,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll be faster?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.04,0:04:35.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:38.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.60,0:04:40.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a genius, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:42.61,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get cocky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.39,0:04:46.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.29,0:04:46.98,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.40,0:04:55.56,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:04:59.57,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:01.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over here! Look at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:02.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.77,0:05:07.20,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya... Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:15.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Look over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.58,0:05:18.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,My turn next!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.58,0:05:20.59,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anchor Howl!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.83,0:05:22.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, Shunichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.07,0:05:23.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let me play, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.68,0:05:23.71,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:29.16,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,There's no plan, no teamwork... Nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:30.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.83,0:05:33.14,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're building up as much aggro as they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.14,0:05:34.73,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.32,0:05:37.48,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.99,0:05:38.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.41,0:05:41.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Now, take me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.48,0:05:48.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.33,0:05:49.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back already.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:50.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:52.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is my third time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.22,0:05:54.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous of your paper-thin armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:54.77,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:56.50,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:06:00.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's an interesting idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.10,0:06:03.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's a revival device...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:05.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it acts as a beacon for people \Nwho are coming back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.86,0:06:12.23,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Someone must have invented it. \NQuite impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.66,0:06:14.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Sis Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.00,0:06:16.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You look pale, young Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.63,0:06:18.15,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:19.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,"Interesting"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:21.24,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:22.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:23.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not insane at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.95,0:06:27.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's acting in accordance with this world's laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.96,0:06:29.69,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.69,0:06:34.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And from the look of it, they seem \Nquite willing to donate empathion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If they keep dying that often, \Nthe gathering efficiency will go up a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:40.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a big help to Genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.67,0:06:42.13,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:43.84,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're dying!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.84,0:06:45.56,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We have to do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.56,0:06:49.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They seem to be quite willing, to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.19,0:06:52.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They desire death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.36,0:06:56.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Their life flashing before their eyes, like a drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.51,0:06:59.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I don't really get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.44,0:07:18.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is Londark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:19.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing out of the order in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.10,0:07:22.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The magic railways are functioning well, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.81,0:07:24.12,HUD1,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(422,1)\an7}Londark \N{\fs20}Race/ Elf \NSorcerer, Lv. 92 \NGuild: Plant Hwyaden
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:24.13,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Message from Lord Londark.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:26.10,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's out of order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.99,0:07:28.65,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,So even the loser from Susukino
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.65,0:07:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is treated as a noble, as long \Nas he's an adventurer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:33.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Message from our nightshade servant scouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:37.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Odyssey Knights are battling the wyverns.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.66,0:07:40.08,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They don't need to do that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.59,0:07:42.65,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Send out our servants! Half of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:43.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:46.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Her condition is stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.47,0:07:48.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, activating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:49.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start synchronization with unit 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:51.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Beginning EXP monitoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.16,0:07:53.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Opening party chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.43,0:08:01.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's complete?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.22,0:08:03.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We summon nightshade servants that act as vessels
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the minds of People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:11.61,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,And the experience points they gain \Ngo to the summoner, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.61,0:08:12.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.85,0:08:18.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, even if the servant dies, \Nit doesn't affect them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:24.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we're giving the People \Nof the Land temporary immortality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.31,0:08:27.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The way you laugh is creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:31.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interrupt me when I'm talking, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.98,0:08:32.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow. Ow. Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.35,0:08:35.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So you use this to raise levels?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:37.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty efficient...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh heh, this is fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.02,0:08:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:40.79,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:45.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You adventurers would call it "power leveling."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.25,0:08:48.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:51.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,In ten minutes, we'll begin injecting EXP pots.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.09,0:08:53.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's dangerous! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.55,0:08:57.59,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Mizufa, Kazuhiko is requesting \Nthat the injections be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:00.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about that hypocrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.51,0:09:02.19,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,They're adventurers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:03.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We're People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.91,0:09:06.60,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What do immortals know of war?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:10.86,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's where you go to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.83,0:09:12.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.35,0:09:19.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand why you people have \Ncreated such an inefficient society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.10,0:09:21.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:22.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:24.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nightshade servants?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:26.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where did they come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.28,0:09:28.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No! Protect our shrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.23,0:09:31.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But when it comes to that,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the knowable world is far smaller \Nthan the unknowable one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:41.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The sum of what we can understand isn't \Nmuch bigger than the head of a pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:45.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So it isn't strange at all that I wouldn't \Nunderstand something, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.22,0:09:45.96,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:46.69,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:47.93,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.93,0:09:49.69,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm coming with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.91,0:09:51.01,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Wolfie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.41,0:09:58.03,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Some of the People of the Land \Ncouldn't get away in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:10:00.03,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Wolfie!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.18,0:10:04.93,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hurricane Slash!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.22,0:10:08.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you don't want to go, Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.31,0:10:15.51,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you, Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:19.89,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you come from? \NAnd where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.24,0:10:34.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's the second time you've asked me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.76,0:10:50.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.77,0:10:55.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What were those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.60,0:10:57.07,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They just showed up out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:59.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,When we defeated them, there was \Nno sign of their psyche dissipating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.13,0:11:02.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:05.42,HUD1,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(421,1)\an9)\fs22}Rundel Haus Code \N{\fs18}Race/ Human \NSorcerer, Lv. 58 \NGuild: Log Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:05.42,HUD1 Blue,,0000,0000,0000,,Move Speed Up\NPsych Def Up \NAggro Down\NBonus Attack
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.91,0:11:04.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Are you out of breath?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.89,0:11:07.02,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.02,0:11:08.43,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.83,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:16.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Wolfie! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.82,0:11:22.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're moving the battlefield to the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.62,0:11:26.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nightshade servants have joined the fray.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.01,0:11:27.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.65,0:11:30.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we can ground the wyverns, they're easy prey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:33.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Lure them into the buildings and kill them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.32,0:11:34.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.42,0:11:35.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let a single one escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.97,0:11:37.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Kill! Kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:39.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:40.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.60,0:11:44.65,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:47.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.30,0:11:50.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:52.24,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:54.27,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:56.61,HUD1,R,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs18}Party Chat\N\NTohya\NMinori\NIsuzu\NRundel Haus Code\NSerara\NRoe 2
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.68,0:11:56.61,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:11:57.59,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.06,0:12:01.61,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.26,0:12:03.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:08.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the Odyssey Knights were \Nsupposed to protect people!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:10.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing something so selfish?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.90,0:12:13.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone lives here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.53,0:12:16.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:18.63,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That isn't what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:20.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,There are other ways to fight, aren't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:23.22,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you getting everyone caught up in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.62,0:12:28.35,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And... Why are sacrificing your own lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.35,0:12:30.72,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of this, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.27,0:12:46.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You said we were sacrificing our lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.56,0:12:48.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But in this world, there is no death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:52.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to take your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:53.25,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.28,0:12:57.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We want to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.57,0:12:59.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.83,0:13:02.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.25,0:13:04.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When you die, you can see your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.64,0:13:07.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When you die, you can see a \Nlittle bit of the old world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.76,0:13:10.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You can see that world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.45,0:13:13.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that place is somehow connected to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.36,0:13:18.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we die, and die, and keep dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.96,0:13:22.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, we'll be able to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.30,0:13:25.80,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.42,0:13:30.59,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I was supposed to get married in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.05,0:13:33.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to quit this game then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.52,0:13:36.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I even went to an open house for an apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:39.55,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have a wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.55,0:13:43.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep playing around with this nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.12,0:13:46.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,When my lease is up, I'm going to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.81,0:13:49.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,She's a real handful, that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:52.94,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,She complains every day, because she \Nwants to leave her parents' house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.94,0:13:55.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get her out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.08,0:13:59.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Mentally, she's a little weak, \Nso I need to take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.47,0:14:01.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.22,0:14:05.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You also hate this stupid farce, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.42,0:14:09.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But there are lots of people \NI care about in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.79,0:14:11.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This world
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.86,0:14:13.25,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,is real, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.09,0:14:15.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.19,0:14:22.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A world where you can't die?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.24,0:14:25.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's... That's a game!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.03,0:14:28.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A world like that can't be real!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.98,0:14:33.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's because people like you keep living...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:36.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Because not everyone is dying...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.40,0:14:40.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That we can't leave this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.00,0:14:46.53,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that important
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.69,0:14:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whether you can die or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:52.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:54.51,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.20,0:15:01.66,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.66,0:15:03.12,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Get an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.12,0:15:05.41,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The driver's not going to make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.62,0:15:10.57,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.57,0:15:11.55,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.55,0:15:12.55,Default - flashback,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's Minori!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.74,0:15:26.07,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever died?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.72,0:15:30.63,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever die in the old world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:36.39,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Were you ever so close to \Ndeath that you may as well
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:40.71,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,have been dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:45.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got a problem with me, call the GMs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.64,0:15:47.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If I'm at fault, they'll ban me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.13,0:15:52.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, you die, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.27,0:15:58.68,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.68,0:16:00.56,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I understand wanting to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.14,0:16:02.15,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:05.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.88,0:16:11.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even so... Even so, we...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.47,0:16:16.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.66,0:16:21.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone... Everyone... Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.68,0:16:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is alive in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:34.78,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Even after he couldn't walk anymore, \NTohya was always smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.75,0:16:36.62,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.26,0:16:40.27,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It was because he knew he was powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.29,0:16:44.76,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The world was just too big, too unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.22,0:16:47.77,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And there was nothing we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:49.91,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That was why...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:53.02,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Because he knew that, he tried so hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.14,0:16:59.49,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And even now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.59,0:17:04.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya is crying out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:10.06,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Serara is casting Heartbeat Healing on \Nevery Person of the Land she can find.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.63,0:17:12.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu and Rundel Haus are
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,protecting the people of the town, \Nas they come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.16,0:17:19.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, there's nothing that can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.88,0:17:27.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you're asking me in a place like this, \Nyou must know the answer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:30.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:32.53,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And who am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.43,0:17:34.72,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where have I come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.72,0:17:35.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I going?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.80,0:17:40.63,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,After yesterday, I kept thinking about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.79,0:17:46.98,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I thought and thought, but I couldn't find an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:49.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:52.14,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't resolve myself to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.83,0:17:54.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:17:57.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But I was lucky, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.79,0:17:59.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,To be born in that world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.29,0:18:01.18,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,to be born to my dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.07,0:18:05.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Because there was music there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.66,0:18:10.67,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,When I was sad, when I was in pain, \Nthere were so many different songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.57,0:18:15.38,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been helped by \Nsomeone else, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.87,0:18:18.12,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, this is so terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.04,0:18:20.99,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Only forty-two?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:22.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.21,0:18:25.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,To be unable to sing when you want to cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.19,0:18:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you're angry, when you're having fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.11,0:18:29.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:30.66,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.12,0:18:33.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.75,0:18:35.15,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.15,0:18:36.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.23,0:18:41.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we going and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:42.37,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to pick a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.37,0:18:43.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.48,0:18:48.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to pick a fight with the god who \Nonly made forty-two songs in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.31,0:18:51.63,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to stop until they cry and apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:54.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Miss Isuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.00,0:18:58.12,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Who is Roe 2?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.12,0:18:59.32,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Is that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.21,0:19:03.83,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,what I really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:07.38,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, that doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.82,0:19:10.70,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who she is, \NI want to be friends with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.16,0:19:13.34,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.57,0:19:18.68,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,So I... Who am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.38,0:19:20.63,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I going?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:22.34,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.26,0:19:24.78,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,My wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.25,0:19:29.35,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.66,0:19:36.08,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}At some point the rain stopped, \Nand the town began to sparkle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.57,0:19:31.37,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,A song?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:35.75,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's Isuzu's wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.08,0:19:43.32,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A huge rainbow stands over all the buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:38.86,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Then my wish is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:43.66,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:46.81,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Right now, more than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.81,0:19:50.70,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I want to show this scenery to you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.70,0:19:55.82,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My heartbeat is fluttering.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:55.31,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be a person who can \Nopen new paths, like Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:20:04.20,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Come on! The magic will never fade, even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.86,0:20:00.72,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I am Shiroe's student.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:04.22,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,And you are our big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.20,0:20:11.32,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't be afraid of boredom, \Nand let's, let's, let's go out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:07.65,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You came from far away, \Nand you're going far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.65,0:20:10.85,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, you're here, with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.32,0:20:14.33,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, what a wonderful Wonder World!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:17.86,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}To a place we've never seen before,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.86,0:20:26.09,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'll take your hand, \Nso let's go there now together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:21.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,On this battlefield, that's your answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:25.28,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,On this battlefield, this is my answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:29.09,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Such a wonderful Wonder World
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.46,0:20:29.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even if nothing changes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:31.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I can change some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:32.73,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Is scattered all around this town, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.94,0:20:34.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,At a time like this, when Tohya \Nis lying on the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:43.15,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Even if the future worries me,\Nif I'm with you, what a wonder it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.72,0:20:36.39,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,He'll stand up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.88,0:20:39.82,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt your words will be heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.82,0:20:42.18,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But you're with us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.82,0:20:47.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I heard your wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.77,0:20:48.76,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.85,0:20:51.39,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I like that, Minori.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.39,0:20:52.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.46,0:20:54.86,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your big sister, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.86,0:20:55.77,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.53,0:20:57.53,Default - italics,R,0000,0000,0000,,Summon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.13,0:21:06.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we have a duty, as those who go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.75,0:21:11.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It would be very uncool of me to knock \Naway the hand you're reaching out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.33,0:21:15.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A big sister never abandons her little sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.93,0:21:23.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,An element cluster gets more \Nstable the bigger it gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:25.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But it also behaves in a deterministic manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.50,0:21:28.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And as it does so, it loses little fragments.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.49,0:21:30.88,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.39,0:21:35.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's natural to want all of humanity to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:38.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But that, in the end, is the beginning of sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.42,0:21:40.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.55,0:21:41.33,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.01,0:21:44.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Your words are so inconvenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.07,0:21:49.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This limited protocol even limits the upper \Nbounds of your thinking organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.65,0:21:55.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You live inside this unfair loneliness, \Nlike it's the stone age?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.65,0:21:57.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.70,0:22:00.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But the empathions are shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.48,0:22:05.08,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is your style, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.68,0:22:20.78,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Shogun,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.78,0:22:23.20,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,your servants are being attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.20,0:22:23.98,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.81,0:22:25.57,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.94,0:22:33.22,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,So we meet here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.90,0:24:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Londark stands in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.73,0:24:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He, too, is forced into action by the \Ntwisted thoughts of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.13,0:24:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.55,0:24:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta cannot answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.89,0:24:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya, Isuzu, and the young children \Nstruggle as hard as they can
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.07,0:24:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to find the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.35,0:24:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Birthday Song.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.35,0:24:30.94,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Birthday Song
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.77,0:24:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
